---
title: Trout with Pistachio-Scallion Gremolata with Red Pepper Glaze, Garlic Herb Potatoes & Green Beans
description: This combo of seared steelhead trout (a relative of the salmon) with a slightly sweet red pepper glaze and a crunchy, tangy pistachio-lemon-scallion gremolata topping is swoon-worthy. And that’s before we’ve even gotten into the sides! Sliced potatoes are roasted until crisp outside and tender inside, while green beans and scallions get a dose of luscious garlic-herb butter before roasting to a golden brown. It feels like a fancy meal, but comes together easily in 35 minutes. It’s the height of so-fish-tication. (We’ll show ourselves out, thanks.)
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64ad63cd08c61453c499a95a-63922971.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64ad63cd08c61453c499a95a.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 280 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/trout-with-pistachio-scallion-gremolata-64ad63cd08c61453c499a95a
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring
@Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @Potatoes{16%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds (no need to peel). Trim
@Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed
and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Roughly chop
@Pistachios{1/2%ounce}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon},
@salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender,
~{18-20%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, pat @Steelhead Trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{};
season with a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Place trout, skin sides down, on one side of a second lightly oiled baking
sheet{}. Spread tops with @Red Pepper Jam{1}.

Toss green beans and scallion whites on empty side of sheet with half the garlic
herb butter, salt, and pepper (it's OK if the butter is chunky, it'll melt and
coat the veggies as they cook).

Roast on top rack until trout is cooked through and green beans are browned and
tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine pistachios, scallion greens, @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), a
pinch of salt, and as much lemon zest as you like. Set aside until ready to
serve.

Once potatoes are done, carefully transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Add remaining
garlic herb butter and toss to coat.

Divide potato rounds, trout, and green beans between plates. Top trout with
gremolata; serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Trout is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.